result.execSummary:
The defendant Michael J. Kassner was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 4th Degree Sexual Assault [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.225(3m).
  • Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes:
Obey all of the rules and regulations of supervising probation agent.  Pay supervision fees.  Participate in counseling deemed appropriate by your agent, which may include: alcohol/drug, anger management/DV counseling, psychiatric/psychological, AODA Assessment and follow-through with recommended treatment.  Counseling shall specifically include:  DV Counseling.
*   Pay fine of $500 and court costs including all applicable surcharges.
*   DV Surcharge
*   If unpaid financial obligations remain at discharge or revocation, civil judgment to be entered.
Cooperate with the Child Support Agency to establish paternity and/or to pay child support and make all court appearances in any paternity action and notify CSA w/ any change of employment w/n 48 hours.  May not have contact with MLM - other than approved by family court, unless otherwise permitted by the court/agent.  Comply w/ family court orders.  Court does not object to probation transferring to Ohio.
